Description.LocalizedString:
A torn piece of red and black plaid flannel. The scrap of fabric imbues The Nurse with devastating focus.
  • Allows the Nurse to see the Blink target location.

A parasitic nit comb taken from the clinic. Once the symbol of a deep connection between an anxious patient and her nurse.
  • Decreases the length of Blink Attack lunges by 50%.
  • Increases Bloodpoints for Blink Attack score events by 100%.

A charred and broken pocket watch with rattling pieces. Taken from Nurse Moris' body.
  • Increases the time before The Nurse succumbs to fatigue after Blinking by 20%.

The gasp of surprise collected from an anxious girl which The Nurse was fond of. Twitches vigorously at The Nurse's touch.
  • Blinking past a survivor causes them to scream and awards 200 Bloodpoints for spooking them.

A white and pristine piece of ribbon once attached to a sacred book. Serves as the symbol of a dispute.
  • Adds 1 Blink charge.
  • Increases Blink recharge time by 30%.

A black rope used as a belt in times of mourning. Taken from Father Campbell's body.
  • Increases movement speed after a Blink but before the following fatigue by 30%.

The whistling and rattling breath stolen from Father Campbell. Silently curves and bends at The Nurse's touch.
  • Blink Attacks inflict the Mangled status effect for 70 seconds.

    • Mangled increases time required to heal by 25% and lasts for a set duration or until fully healed.

A powerful last breath snatched from Crotus Prenn asylum priest Father Campbell. In the hands of The Nurse, it crackles with intensity.
  • After reappearing from a fully charged Blink, The Nurse immediately Blinks at full charge in the direction she is currently facing.
  • This only works ifÂ The Nurse has a remaining Blink charge.

A dull, partially rusted and stained metallic spoon. Confiscated from room 202's patient, the "Bad Man".
  • Hitting a survivor with a successful Blink Attack causes their sounds of pain to be 50% louder for 60 seconds.

A rotten molar extirpated from the "Bad Man's" cold dead hand.
  • Hitting a survivor with a successful Blink Attack causes their aura to be revealed when healing or being healed within a 28 meter range for 60 seconds.

An unpainted toy carved out of cheap wood to resemble a horse. Once the symbol of a deep connection between a catatonic patient and his nurse.
  • Decreases extra fatigue from missed Blink Attacks by 50%.

A pine-cone which unexpectedly calmed a patient's repetitive movement. Taken from the catatonic boy's body.
  • Decreases extra fatigue from chain Blinks by 65%.

The irregular and deteriorating breath collected from the catatonic boy. Normally stable and calm, becomes incredibly agitated at The Nurse's touch.
  • Decreases base Blink fatigue duration by 7%.

A powerful last breath snatched from Crotus Prenn asylum patient "the Bad Man." In the hands of The Nurse, it jolts with intensity.
  • Hitting a survivor with a successful Blink Attack grants the Nurse Undetectable for 25 seconds. This effect may be only triggered once every 45 seconds.

    • Undetectable hides the Killer's aura, Terror Radius, and Red Stain.

A worthless piece of jewelry that might have had an important significance to someone. Taken from the anxious girl's body.
  • Decreases maximum Blink distance by 20%.
  • Increases Bloodpoints for Precise Blink score events by 100%.

The slow and bulging breath stolen from the orderly. Dimly oscillates at The Nurse's touch.
  • Extends the duration of a lunge after more than one Blink by 30%.

A powerful last breath snatched from Crotus Prenn asylum patient Mary Jenner. In the hands of The Nurse, it trembles with intensity.
  • OnceÂ The Nurse has exhausted allÂ of herÂ Blinks, allowsÂ The NurseÂ to immediately Blink back to her original position by pressing theÂ Active Ability Button.
  • Must be triggered beforeÂ The NurseÂ succumbs to fatigue.
  • After returning to her original position, The Nurse will have one Blink charge ready.

A powerful last breath snatched from Crotus Prenn asylum orderly Harvey Kavanagh. In the hands of The Nurse, it wobbles with intensity.
  • When succumbing to fatigue, any Survivors within 8 meters of The Nurse are afflicted with the Blindness status effect for 60 seconds.

    • Blindness prevents Survivors from seeing auras.

A matchbox containing an odd collection of mismatched buttons. Serves as a reminder of a horrible place.
  • Sets maximum number of Blink charges to 1.
  • Increases The Nurse's base movement speed to 4.4 m/s.

The twitchy and tremulous breath stolen from the "Bad Man." Aggressively pulses and jumps at The Nurse's touch.
  • Hitting a survivor with a successful Blink Attack disables the ability to Blink and increases the Nurse's base movement speed to 4.6 m/s for 60 seconds.
